IMPORT prelude
IMPORT `housing-act-common`
IMPORT daydate

§ `Housing Act 1988 — Schedule 2 — Part I — Ground 6B (Renters' Rights Act 2025)`

-- ===========================================================================
-- GROUND 6B — the "enforcement" MANDATORY ground, inserted into Schedule 2 to
-- the Housing Act 1988 by the Renters' Rights Act 2025 (c. 26), s. 145(1)(8),
-- Sch. 1 para. 22 (with ss. 138, 146(1), Sch. 6 paras. 1, 3, 4, 16, 17);
-- commencement 1.5.2026 for specified purposes; S.I. 2026/421, reg. 2(b),
-- marker F40. Part I (mandatory): where made out, the court MUST order
-- possession.
--
-- HYBRID encoding:
--   * the constitutive conditions -> predicates carrying the verbatim statute
--     inline as inert prose; only the operative atoms are lifted;
--   * the mandatory outcome       -> a guarded deontic clause.
--
-- Statutory text encoded ("Any of the following applies—", a DISJUNCTION over
-- (a)-(g)):
--   (a) letting the dwelling-house causes the landlord to breach a banning order
--       under section 16 of the Housing and Planning Act 2016, or would do so if
--       the landlord were to continue to let the dwelling-house;
--   (b) an improvement notice under section 11 or 12 of the Housing Act 2004—
--         (i)  specifies the dwelling-house or premises in which the dwelling-
--              house is contained as requiring remedial action, and
--         (ii) specifies overcrowding as the deficiency giving rise to the hazard
--              in respect of which that remedial action is to be taken;
--   (c) a prohibition order under section 20 or 21 of the Housing Act 2004
--       prohibits use of—
--         (i)   the dwelling-house,
--         (ii)  the common parts, or
--         (iii) any part of the dwelling-house or of the common parts,
--       either for all purposes or for any purpose that is incompatible with
--       continued occupation by the tenant;
--   (d) the dwelling-house is or is in an HMO which is required to be licensed
--       under section 61 of the Housing Act 2004, and—
--         (i)  the landlord applied for a licence under section 63 of the Housing
--              Act 2004 and the local housing authority refused to grant a
--              licence, or
--         (ii) the landlord held a licence but the licence has been revoked;
--   (e) the dwelling-house is or is in a house which is required to be licensed
--       under section 85 of the Housing Act 2004, and—
--         (i)  the landlord applied for a licence under section 87 of the Housing
--              Act 2004 and the local housing authority refused to grant a
--              licence, or
--         (ii) the landlord held a licence but the licence has been revoked;
--   (f) the dwelling-house is or is in an HMO which is licensed under Part 2 of
--       the Housing Act 2004 or a house which is licensed under Part 3 of that
--       Act and that HMO or house is occupied by more than the maximum number of
--       households or persons specified in the licence;
--   (g) compliance with a planning enforcement notice or injunction would be, or
--       is, incompatible with continued occupation of the dwelling-house by the
--       tenant.
--
-- INTERPRETATION CALLS flagged for the human reviewer:
--   * Made out = (a) OR (b) OR (c) OR (d) OR (e) OR (f) OR (g) — a top-level
--     DISJUNCTION; each disjunct is spelled with its own sub-structure.
--   * (a) is itself a DISJUNCTION: letting causes a breach now OR would cause one
--       on continued letting.
--   * (b) is a CONJUNCTION of (i) AND (ii) (the notice both specifies the
--       dwelling-house as requiring remedial action AND specifies overcrowding as
--       the hazard deficiency).
--   * (c) is a CONJUNCTION: the prohibition order prohibits use of one or more of
--       (i)/(ii)/(iii) (a DISJUNCTION) AND that prohibition is for all purposes or
--       for a purpose incompatible with continued occupation (a DISJUNCTION).
--   * (d) and (e) are each a CONJUNCTION of the licensing-requirement chapeau
--       AND a DISJUNCTION over (i) OR (ii) (refusal of a licence application OR
--       revocation of a held licence). They differ only in the HA2004 sections:
--       (d) HMO s.61/s.63; (e) house s.85/s.87.
--   * (f) is a CONJUNCTION: licensed (Part 2 HMO .. Part 3 house) AND over the
--       maximum number specified in the licence.
--   * (g) is a single operative atom.
--   * The "In this ground—" definitions ("common parts" as in Ground 13; "house"
--     as in Part 3 HA2004; the joint-landlords reading of "landlord"; the
--     "planning enforcement notice or injunction" enumeration; "P(LBCA)A 1990";
--     "TCPA 1990"; "the local housing authority" per s.261 HA2004) are carried
--     as inert prose; their operative effect is folded into the lifted atoms
--     (e.g. `compliance with a planning enforcement notice or injunction ...`).
--   * "landlord" reads, per the joint-landlords rule, as "the landlord seeking
--     possession or, where joint, at least one of them".
-- ===========================================================================

§§ `Domain model`

-- Actor (Landlord, Tenant, Court) is imported from `housing-act-common`.

-- The operative atoms of disjuncts (a)-(g), gathered on the claim.
DECLARE Ground6BClaim HAS
  -- (a)
  `letting the dwelling-house causes the landlord to breach a section 16 banning order`         IS A BOOLEAN
  `letting would cause a breach if the landlord were to continue to let the dwelling-house`      IS A BOOLEAN
  -- (b)
  `an improvement notice under s.11 or s.12 HA2004 specifies the dwelling-house or premises as requiring remedial action`  IS A BOOLEAN
  `that improvement notice specifies overcrowding as the deficiency giving rise to the hazard`   IS A BOOLEAN
  -- (c)
  `a prohibition order under s.20 or s.21 HA2004 prohibits use of the dwelling-house`            IS A BOOLEAN  -- (c)(i)
  `that prohibition order prohibits use of the common parts`                                     IS A BOOLEAN  -- (c)(ii)
  `that prohibition order prohibits use of any part of the dwelling-house or of the common parts`  IS A BOOLEAN  -- (c)(iii)
  `the prohibition is for all purposes`                                                          IS A BOOLEAN
  `the prohibition is for a purpose incompatible with continued occupation by the tenant`        IS A BOOLEAN
  -- (d)
  `the dwelling-house is or is in an HMO required to be licensed under s.61 HA2004`              IS A BOOLEAN
  `the landlord applied for a licence under s.63 HA2004 and the local housing authority refused to grant a licence`  IS A BOOLEAN  -- (d)(i)
  `the landlord held an s.61 HMO licence but the licence has been revoked`                       IS A BOOLEAN  -- (d)(ii)
  -- (e)
  `the dwelling-house is or is in a house required to be licensed under s.85 HA2004`             IS A BOOLEAN
  `the landlord applied for a licence under s.87 HA2004 and the local housing authority refused to grant a licence`  IS A BOOLEAN  -- (e)(i)
  `the landlord held an s.85 house licence but the licence has been revoked`                     IS A BOOLEAN  -- (e)(ii)
  -- (f)
  `the dwelling-house is or is in an HMO licensed under Part 2 HA2004 or a house licensed under Part 3 HA2004`  IS A BOOLEAN
  `that HMO or house is occupied by more than the maximum number of households or persons specified in the licence`  IS A BOOLEAN
  -- (g)
  `compliance with a planning enforcement notice or injunction would be or is incompatible with continued occupation by the tenant`  IS A BOOLEAN

§§ `(a) — letting breaches, or on continued letting would breach, a banning order`

GIVEN claim IS A Ground6BClaim
GIVETH A BOOLEAN
`(a) — banning-order breach` claim MEANS
        "(a) letting the dwelling-house causes the landlord to breach a banning order under section 16 of the Housing and Planning Act 2016,"
    ..  claim's `letting the dwelling-house causes the landlord to breach a section 16 banning order`
    ..  "or would do so if the landlord were to continue to let the dwelling-house;"
    ..  claim's `letting would cause a breach if the landlord were to continue to let the dwelling-house`

§§ `(b) — improvement notice specifying the dwelling-house and citing overcrowding`

GIVEN claim IS A Ground6BClaim
GIVETH A BOOLEAN
`(b) — improvement notice for overcrowding` claim MEANS
        "(b) an improvement notice under section 11 or 12 of the Housing Act 2004—"
    ...     "(i) specifies the dwelling-house or premises in which the dwelling-house is contained as requiring remedial action, and"
        ... claim's `an improvement notice under s.11 or s.12 HA2004 specifies the dwelling-house or premises as requiring remedial action`
    AND     "(ii) specifies overcrowding as the deficiency giving rise to the hazard in respect of which that remedial action is to be taken;"
        ... claim's `that improvement notice specifies overcrowding as the deficiency giving rise to the hazard`

§§ `(c) — prohibition order prohibiting use, for all or incompatible purposes`

-- (c) prohibits use of one or more of (i)/(ii)/(iii), AND that prohibition is
-- either for all purposes or for a purpose incompatible with continued occupation.
GIVEN claim IS A Ground6BClaim
GIVETH A BOOLEAN
`(c) — prohibition order incompatible with occupation` claim MEANS
        "(c) a prohibition order under section 20 or 21 of the Housing Act 2004 prohibits use of—"
    ...     "(i) the dwelling-house,"
        ..  claim's `a prohibition order under s.20 or s.21 HA2004 prohibits use of the dwelling-house`
        ..  "(ii) the common parts, or"
        ..  claim's `that prohibition order prohibits use of the common parts`
        ..  "(iii) any part of the dwelling-house or of the common parts,"
        ..  claim's `that prohibition order prohibits use of any part of the dwelling-house or of the common parts`
    AND     "either for all purposes or for any purpose that is incompatible with continued occupation by the tenant;"
        ..  claim's `the prohibition is for all purposes`
        ..  claim's `the prohibition is for a purpose incompatible with continued occupation by the tenant`

§§ `(d) — required s.61 HMO licence: application refused or licence revoked`

GIVEN claim IS A Ground6BClaim
GIVETH A BOOLEAN
`(d) — HMO licensing failure under s.61` claim MEANS
        "(d) the dwelling-house is or is in an HMO which is required to be licensed under section 61 of the Housing Act 2004, and—"
    ... claim's `the dwelling-house is or is in an HMO required to be licensed under s.61 HA2004`
    AND     "(i) the landlord applied for a licence under section 63 of the Housing Act 2004 and the local housing authority refused to grant a licence, or"
        ..  claim's `the landlord applied for a licence under s.63 HA2004 and the local housing authority refused to grant a licence`
        ..  "(ii) the landlord held a licence but the licence has been revoked;"
        ..  claim's `the landlord held an s.61 HMO licence but the licence has been revoked`

§§ `(e) — required s.85 house licence: application refused or licence revoked`

GIVEN claim IS A Ground6BClaim
GIVETH A BOOLEAN
`(e) — house licensing failure under s.85` claim MEANS
        "(e) the dwelling-house is or is in a house which is required to be licensed under section 85 of the Housing Act 2004, and—"
    ... claim's `the dwelling-house is or is in a house required to be licensed under s.85 HA2004`
    AND     "(i) the landlord applied for a licence under section 87 of the Housing Act 2004 and the local housing authority refused to grant a licence, or"
        ..  claim's `the landlord applied for a licence under s.87 HA2004 and the local housing authority refused to grant a licence`
        ..  "(ii) the landlord held a licence but the licence has been revoked;"
        ..  claim's `the landlord held an s.85 house licence but the licence has been revoked`

§§ `(f) — licensed HMO/house occupied over the licensed maximum`

GIVEN claim IS A Ground6BClaim
GIVETH A BOOLEAN
`(f) — licensed dwelling occupied over the maximum` claim MEANS
        "(f) the dwelling-house is or is in an HMO which is licensed under Part 2 of the Housing Act 2004 or a house which is licensed under Part 3 of that Act"
    ... claim's `the dwelling-house is or is in an HMO licensed under Part 2 HA2004 or a house licensed under Part 3 HA2004`
    AND "and that HMO or house is occupied by more than the maximum number of households or persons specified in the licence;"
    ... claim's `that HMO or house is occupied by more than the maximum number of households or persons specified in the licence`

§§ `(g) — planning enforcement notice or injunction incompatible with occupation`

-- "planning enforcement notice or injunction" means: (a) a TCPA 1990 s.172/182
-- enforcement notice that has taken effect, (b) a TCPA 1990 s.187A breach of
-- condition notice, (c) a TCPA 1990 s.187B injunction, (d) a P(LBCA)A 1990
-- s.38/45/46 listed building enforcement notice that has taken effect, or (e) a
-- P(LBCA)A 1990 s.44A injunction. (carried as inert prose; "P(LBCA)A 1990" = the
-- Planning (Listed Building and Conservation Areas) Act 1990; "TCPA 1990" = the
-- Town and Country Planning Act 1990.)
GIVEN claim IS A Ground6BClaim
GIVETH A BOOLEAN
`(g) — planning enforcement incompatible with occupation` claim MEANS
        "(g) compliance with a planning enforcement notice or injunction would be, or is, incompatible with continued occupation of the dwelling-house by the tenant."
    ... claim's `compliance with a planning enforcement notice or injunction would be or is incompatible with continued occupation by the tenant`

§§ `Ground 6B made out — any of (a)-(g) applies`

GIVEN claim IS A Ground6BClaim
GIVETH A BOOLEAN
`Ground 6B made out` claim MEANS
        "Any of the following applies—"
    ..  `(a) — banning-order breach` claim
    ..  `(b) — improvement notice for overcrowding` claim
    ..  `(c) — prohibition order incompatible with occupation` claim
    ..  `(d) — HMO licensing failure under s.61` claim
    ..  `(e) — house licensing failure under s.85` claim
    ..  `(f) — licensed dwelling occupied over the maximum` claim
    ..  `(g) — planning enforcement incompatible with occupation` claim

§§ `The mandatory outcome — Court MUST order possession`

-- Action (`order possession`) is imported from `housing-act-common`.

GIVEN claim IS A Ground6BClaim
GIVETH A DEONTIC Actor Action
`ground 6B possession order` claim MEANS
    IF   `Ground 6B made out` claim
    THEN PARTY Court MUST `order possession` WITHIN 30
    ELSE FULFILLED


§ `Tests`

-- ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Each test scenario is a FULLY-SPELLED Ground6BClaim value (the house style;
-- L4 has no record-update). The all-false base sets every atom FALSE -> no
-- disjunct fires. Then one positive scenario per disjunct (a)-(g), each lighting
-- up exactly that disjunct's atoms (and nothing else), so a single TRUE disjunct
-- carries the whole top-level OR.
-- ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

§§ `All-false base — no disjunct applies -> NOT made out`

`base — all false` MEANS Ground6BClaim WITH
  `letting the dwelling-house causes the landlord to breach a section 16 banning order`         IS FALSE
  `letting would cause a breach if the landlord were to continue to let the dwelling-house`      IS FALSE
  `an improvement notice under s.11 or s.12 HA2004 specifies the dwelling-house or premises as requiring remedial action`  IS FALSE
  `that improvement notice specifies overcrowding as the deficiency giving rise to the hazard`   IS FALSE
  `a prohibition order under s.20 or s.21 HA2004 prohibits use of the dwelling-house`            IS FALSE
  `that prohibition order prohibits use of the common parts`                                     IS FALSE
  `that prohibition order prohibits use of any part of the dwelling-house or of the common parts`  IS FALSE
  `the prohibition is for all purposes`                                                          IS FALSE
  `the prohibition is for a purpose incompatible with continued occupation by the tenant`        IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house is or is in an HMO required to be licensed under s.61 HA2004`              IS FALSE
  `the landlord applied for a licence under s.63 HA2004 and the local housing authority refused to grant a licence`  IS FALSE
  `the landlord held an s.61 HMO licence but the licence has been revoked`                       IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house is or is in a house required to be licensed under s.85 HA2004`             IS FALSE
  `the landlord applied for a licence under s.87 HA2004 and the local housing authority refused to grant a licence`  IS FALSE
  `the landlord held an s.85 house licence but the licence has been revoked`                     IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house is or is in an HMO licensed under Part 2 HA2004 or a house licensed under Part 3 HA2004`  IS FALSE
  `that HMO or house is occupied by more than the maximum number of households or persons specified in the licence`  IS FALSE
  `compliance with a planning enforcement notice or injunction would be or is incompatible with continued occupation by the tenant`  IS FALSE

#ASSERT NOT `(a) — banning-order breach`                          `base — all false`
#ASSERT NOT `(b) — improvement notice for overcrowding`          `base — all false`
#ASSERT NOT `(c) — prohibition order incompatible with occupation` `base — all false`
#ASSERT NOT `(d) — HMO licensing failure under s.61`             `base — all false`
#ASSERT NOT `(e) — house licensing failure under s.85`           `base — all false`
#ASSERT NOT `(f) — licensed dwelling occupied over the maximum`  `base — all false`
#ASSERT NOT `(g) — planning enforcement incompatible with occupation` `base — all false`
#ASSERT NOT `Ground 6B made out`                                 `base — all false`

§§ `(a) made out — letting would breach a banning order on continued letting`

`claim via (a)` MEANS Ground6BClaim WITH
  `letting the dwelling-house causes the landlord to breach a section 16 banning order`         IS FALSE
  `letting would cause a breach if the landlord were to continue to let the dwelling-house`      IS TRUE
  `an improvement notice under s.11 or s.12 HA2004 specifies the dwelling-house or premises as requiring remedial action`  IS FALSE
  `that improvement notice specifies overcrowding as the deficiency giving rise to the hazard`   IS FALSE
  `a prohibition order under s.20 or s.21 HA2004 prohibits use of the dwelling-house`            IS FALSE
  `that prohibition order prohibits use of the common parts`                                     IS FALSE
  `that prohibition order prohibits use of any part of the dwelling-house or of the common parts`  IS FALSE
  `the prohibition is for all purposes`                                                          IS FALSE
  `the prohibition is for a purpose incompatible with continued occupation by the tenant`        IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house is or is in an HMO required to be licensed under s.61 HA2004`              IS FALSE
  `the landlord applied for a licence under s.63 HA2004 and the local housing authority refused to grant a licence`  IS FALSE
  `the landlord held an s.61 HMO licence but the licence has been revoked`                       IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house is or is in a house required to be licensed under s.85 HA2004`             IS FALSE
  `the landlord applied for a licence under s.87 HA2004 and the local housing authority refused to grant a licence`  IS FALSE
  `the landlord held an s.85 house licence but the licence has been revoked`                     IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house is or is in an HMO licensed under Part 2 HA2004 or a house licensed under Part 3 HA2004`  IS FALSE
  `that HMO or house is occupied by more than the maximum number of households or persons specified in the licence`  IS FALSE
  `compliance with a planning enforcement notice or injunction would be or is incompatible with continued occupation by the tenant`  IS FALSE

#ASSERT `(a) — banning-order breach` `claim via (a)`
#ASSERT `Ground 6B made out`         `claim via (a)`

§§ `(b) made out — improvement notice specifies dwelling-house AND overcrowding`

-- (b) needs BOTH (i) AND (ii). The all-met-(b) scenario sets both TRUE.
`claim via (b)` MEANS Ground6BClaim WITH
  `letting the dwelling-house causes the landlord to breach a section 16 banning order`         IS FALSE
  `letting would cause a breach if the landlord were to continue to let the dwelling-house`      IS FALSE
  `an improvement notice under s.11 or s.12 HA2004 specifies the dwelling-house or premises as requiring remedial action`  IS TRUE
  `that improvement notice specifies overcrowding as the deficiency giving rise to the hazard`   IS TRUE
  `a prohibition order under s.20 or s.21 HA2004 prohibits use of the dwelling-house`            IS FALSE
  `that prohibition order prohibits use of the common parts`                                     IS FALSE
  `that prohibition order prohibits use of any part of the dwelling-house or of the common parts`  IS FALSE
  `the prohibition is for all purposes`                                                          IS FALSE
  `the prohibition is for a purpose incompatible with continued occupation by the tenant`        IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house is or is in an HMO required to be licensed under s.61 HA2004`              IS FALSE
  `the landlord applied for a licence under s.63 HA2004 and the local housing authority refused to grant a licence`  IS FALSE
  `the landlord held an s.61 HMO licence but the licence has been revoked`                       IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house is or is in a house required to be licensed under s.85 HA2004`             IS FALSE
  `the landlord applied for a licence under s.87 HA2004 and the local housing authority refused to grant a licence`  IS FALSE
  `the landlord held an s.85 house licence but the licence has been revoked`                     IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house is or is in an HMO licensed under Part 2 HA2004 or a house licensed under Part 3 HA2004`  IS FALSE
  `that HMO or house is occupied by more than the maximum number of households or persons specified in the licence`  IS FALSE
  `compliance with a planning enforcement notice or injunction would be or is incompatible with continued occupation by the tenant`  IS FALSE

#ASSERT `(b) — improvement notice for overcrowding` `claim via (b)`
#ASSERT `Ground 6B made out`                        `claim via (b)`

§§ `(b) knocked out — improvement notice specifies dwelling-house but NOT overcrowding`

-- (b)(ii) missing: only (i) is set, so the (i) AND (ii) conjunction fails.
`claim via (b) — no overcrowding` MEANS Ground6BClaim WITH
  `letting the dwelling-house causes the landlord to breach a section 16 banning order`         IS FALSE
  `letting would cause a breach if the landlord were to continue to let the dwelling-house`      IS FALSE
  `an improvement notice under s.11 or s.12 HA2004 specifies the dwelling-house or premises as requiring remedial action`  IS TRUE
  `that improvement notice specifies overcrowding as the deficiency giving rise to the hazard`   IS FALSE
